Design Patterns

A structure that provides typical solutions to common problems in software design.

Each pattern is like a template that you can customize to solve a particular design problem in your code.

- Creational Design Patterns

- Structural Design Patterns

- Behavioural Design Patterns

1. Decorator Pattern

Structural Pattern - Allows us to add new functionalities or responsibilities to existing objects without affecting
the behaviour of other existing objects.

Sometimes called the 'wrapper pattern'